Came in for dinner. I had the Pot Roast Dip with baked mac and cheese for the side, my wife had the Mihami Vice with fruit for the side. We also shared an order of the Party Tots. First the good. My wife’s Mihami was pretty solid. Everything thing else was pretty rough. Pot Roast Dip was bland, and messy. The sweetness of the jalapeño jelly overpowered any other flavors. The baked mac and cheese didn’t appear baked at all. No brown or crust, just flavorless cheap-buffet-style mac and cheese. The tots tasted like freezer burn and were undercooked so that they were soft and not crispy. Beer cheese sauce on tots was also bland. Sandwiches are my favorite food and I was so excited to try this restaurant but was so incredibly disappointed.

Their prices are considerably high for the sandwich outcome and any sandwich that you purchase could not compare to Uncle Giuseppe's or a number of other Italian sandwich joints in Boise. Their customer service is varying from month to month as they have a high turnover rate for employees. Recently I went to the store on my mother's birthday their sugar cookies are her favorite dessert.granted it was at exactly 4 p.m. when they closed, however a rude employee informed me before I even asked her or gave her information about what I was asking, that registers were closed and she couldn't help me. As I have worked in the culinary industry, it is a terrible business model to turn away customers if it's a quick cash exchange when you still have customers dining in in the restaurant. That makes absolutely no sense from a customer service model or a business model, it's just being lazy and inconsiderate. I'm sure it was just the waitress and she wanted to go home and was being a jerk however this definitely cast a light over Even Stevens customer service for me, and I will not be back in the future.
